Please repeat it in 3 months time - if still raised we want to recommend a consult with Dr Riaz for an assessment and the way forward
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Clinical Recommendations: Normal clinical examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Total Cholesterol 7.7, LDL 5.9, Non-HDL 6.3
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Suboptimal Vit D
Slightly raised uric acid
Abnormal lung function
Increased BMI
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Overview Notes: Your Lipogram is significantly deranged, more so than last year. You have improved your lifestyle. You exercise regularly. We recommend an Omega 3 supplement and a RQ10 supplement. Please repeat it in 3 months time - if still raised we want to recommend a consult with Dr Riaz for an assessment and the way forward
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Report Date: 2021-11-17
Doctor: Carla Marais
Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Your Lipogram is significantly deranged, more so than last year. You have improved your lifestyle. You exercise regularly. We recommend an Omega 3 supplement and a RQ10 supplement. Please repeat it in 3 months time - if still raised we want to recommend a consult with Dr Riaz for an assessment and the way forward
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Vit D can be supplemented with Vit D3 5000iu daily and a repeat is recommended in 3 months time.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Overview Notes: Uric Acid: reduce red meat and keep alcohol intake low
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Diet can contribute to a lot to wellbeing. A dietician can assist in helping with a meal plan that can assist in improving your wellbeing. They can review what we might think to consider a healthy diet and assist in areas we do not expect.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Your lung function test is abnormal. The FEV1% is 60%. This can be normal in previous Asthma, however if symptomatic - please get a pulmonology assessment.

Overview Notes: Your Lipogram is significantly deranged, more so than last year. You have improved your lifestyle. You exercise regularly. We recommend an Omega 3 supplement and a RQ10 supplement. Please repeat it in 3 months time - if still raised we want to recommend a consult with Dr Riaz for an assessment and the way forward
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Please repeat it in 3 months time - if still raised we want to recommend a consult with Dr Riaz for an assessment and the way forward
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Please repeat it in 3 months time - if still raised we want to recommend a consult with Dr Riaz for an assessment and the way forward
Comment Key: ClinicalExamNote
Comment Value: Abnormal gait due to ankle injury and surgery
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Comment Value: Abnormal gait due to ankle injury and surgery
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Overview Notes: Diet can contribute to a lot to wellbeing. A dietician can assist in helping with a meal plan that can assist in improving your wellbeing. They can review what we might think to consider a healthy diet and assist in areas we do not expect.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Your Lipogram is significantly deranged, more so than last year. You have improved your lifestyle. You exercise regularly. We recommend an Omega 3 supplement and a RQ10 supplement. Please repeat it in 3 months time - if still raised we want to recommend a consult with Dr Riaz for an assessment and the way forward
Comment Key: CurrentComplaintNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Vit D can be supplemented with Vit D3 5000iu daily and a repeat is recommended in 3 months time.
Comment Key: CurrentComplaintNote

Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year

Overview Notes: Your Lipogram is significantly deranged, more so than last year. You have improved your lifestyle. You exercise regularly. We recommend an Omega 3 supplement and a RQ10 supplement. Please repeat it in 3 months time - if still raised we want to recommend a consult with Dr Riaz for an assessment and the way forward
Comment Key: EyesightRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Overview Notes: Vit D can be supplemented with Vit D3 5000iu daily and a repeat is recommended in 3 months time.
Comment Key: LabTestNote
Comment Value: Liver Enzymes greatly improved form last year
Total cholesterol significantly raised, as well as LDL, nonHDL
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Total Cholesterol 7.7, LDL 5.9, Non-HDL 6.3
Comment Key: LabTestNote
Comment Value: Liver Enzymes greatly improved form last year
Total cholesterol significantly raised, as well as LDL, nonHDL
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Your lung function test is abnormal. The FEV1% is 60%. This can be normal in previous Asthma, however if symptomatic - please get a pulmonology assessment.
Comment Key: LabTestRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Overview Notes: Diet can contribute to a lot to wellbeing. A dietician can assist in helping with a meal plan that can assist in improving your wellbeing. They can review what we might think to consider a healthy diet and assist in areas we do not expect.
Comment Key: LifestyleNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Normal examination on the day.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Your Lipogram is significantly deranged, more so than last year. You have improved your lifestyle. You exercise regularly. We recommend an Omega 3 supplement and a RQ10 supplement. Overview Notes: Improved body fat percentage despite major setback with ankle injury
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Uric Acid: reduce red meat and keep alcohol intake low
Comment Key: MedicalHistoryNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Comment Value: Cancer has preventable (smoking, alcohol, weight) and non-preventable (genes, age, gender, race) risk factors. Try your best to reduce your risk of preventable factors.
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Overview Notes: Diet can contribute to a lot to wellbeing. A dietician can assist in helping with a meal plan that can assist in improving your wellbeing. They can review what we might think to consider a healthy diet and assist in areas we do not expect.
Comment Key: MentalHealthMoodRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Comment Key: MentalHealthStressRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Overview Notes: Diet can contribute to a lot to wellbeing. A dietician can assist in helping with a meal plan that can assist in improving your wellbeing. They can review what we might think to consider a healthy diet and assist in areas we do not expect.
Comment Key: ReportNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Comment Key: SpecialInvestigationRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Women's Health Recommendations:

Men's Health Recommendations: Please report any new urinary symptoms to your doctor.

Comment Value: Ideal wight to height ratio is <50%, BMI ideally <25
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Total Cholesterol 7.7, LDL 5.9, Non-HDL 6.3
Comment Key: VitalsNote
Comment Value: Ideal wight to height ratio is <50%, BMI ideally <25
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Overview Notes: Diet can contribute to a lot to wellbeing. A dietician can assist in helping with a meal plan that can assist in improving your wellbeing. They can review what we might think to consider a healthy diet and assist in areas we do not expect.
Comment Key: VitalsRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Overview Notes: Diet can contribute to a lot to wellbeing. A dietician can assist in helping with a meal plan that can assist in improving your wellbeing. They can review what we might think to consider a healthy diet and assist in areas we do not expect.
Comment Key: VitalsRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Clinical Recommendations: 
Men's Health Recommendations: Please report any new urinary symptoms to your doctor.
Women's Health Recommendations: 
Overview Notes: Diet can contribute to a lot to wellbeing. A dietician can assist in helping with a meal plan that can assist in improving your wellbeing. They can review what we might think to consider a healthy diet and assist in areas we do not expect.
Comment Key: VitaminsOrSupplements
Comment Value: Vitamin D , Vitamin B co
Special Investigation Notes: Body Fat Percentage improved from 24.8% to 22.6% this year
Abnormal Lung Function - if symptomatic, get a review by a pulmonologist, FEV1% 60%

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels

Abnormal lung function
Increased BMI

Men's Health Recommendations: PSA testing annually from age 40. Elevated PSA level doesn't necessarily indicate prostate cancer. Other conditions, such as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) and prostate infections, can also lead to increased PSA levels
Women's Health Recommendations:
